fetch_ticket.result:
Title: [Cloud And On-prem] OtlpspanEvents do not have span attributes  HTTP_REFERER and HTTP_RESPONSE_REDIRECT_LOCATION

Components: Telemetry Infrastructure

Description:
Please look at this Trace I couldn't able to find where this request is redirected to. This is a CLM Demo Trace; Can you please take a look why OtlpSpanEvents do not have span attributes  HTTP_REFERER and HTTP_RESPONSE_REDIRECT_LOCATION ?
Query from OtlpSpanEvents 
Query from RequestEvents link here
As you know that these are very important span attributes for us to assess the impact and for investigation of an issue, could you please ensure these attributes are available in OtlpspanEvents? Thank youimage-20250513-205615.png|width=1710,height=767,alt="image-20250513-205615.png"!

result.semantic_description: Ensure OTLP span events include the HTTP_REFERER and HTTP_RESPONSE_REDIRECT_LOCATION attributes.

sub_tasks.description: Confirm with Privacy / Sec-Ops that capturing these two headers is compliant in all regions. Verify that the header-scrubber config already whitelists them or add exceptions.
sub_tasks.validation_criteria: Written approval stored in the ticket; headers added to scrubber whitelist file.

sub_tasks.description:
Locate where HTTP server/client spans are created and finalized.
• Search for `setAttribute("http.method"` etc. to find the core helper.
• Identify both cloud runtime path (`CloudHttpSpanBuilder.java`) and on-prem path (`OnPremHttpTelemetryMiddleware.cs`).
sub_tasks.validation_criteria: Exact methods that call `span.setAttribute(...)` are listed in the ticket wiki.

sub_tasks.description:
Document how the new attributes are added:
• Server side – before response is committed so status and Location header are visible.
• Client side – after we receive the response.
• Attribute names MUST follow existing casing (`http.referer`, `http.response.redirect_location`) to stay OTEL-semantic-convention compliant.
• Values MUST go through `HeaderScrubber.scrub(String)`.
sub_tasks.validation_criteria: Design doc attached and approved in pull-request #12345.

sub_tasks.description:
Modify `CloudHttpSpanBuilder.java`:
1. Read `Referer` header from `HttpServletRequest` and call `span.setAttribute("http.referer", scrub(value))`.
2. After `chain.doFilter`, if `3xx`, fetch `Location` header from `HttpServletResponse` and set `span.setAttribute("http.response.redirect_location", scrub(value))`.
sub_tasks.validation_criteria: Unit tests in `CloudHttpSpanBuilderTest` assert attributes exist.

sub_tasks.description:
Update `OnPremHttpTelemetryMiddleware.cs` similarly:
• Before calling next middleware – capture Referer.
• After next middleware – inspect response.StatusCode 300-399 and Location header.
• Use `Span.SetAttribute()`.
Add logic to redact query-string tokens that match PII patterns and limit value length (<=256 chars).
sub_tasks.validation_criteria: Scrubber unit tests cover new headers.

sub_tasks.description:
• Spin up docker compose demo (cloud) and local IIS site (on-prem).
• Trigger a 302 redirect flow.
• Validate via OTLP collector that spans now show both attributes.
sub_tasks.validation_criteria: New Cypress job in CI reports attributes present.

sub_tasks.description: Update internal schema doc + Grafana data-source mapping so new attributes appear in drop-downs. Announce in #telemetry-announce.
Deploy to staging, then to 5% of production pods in both SaaS regions. Monitor span volume and verify no cardinality explosions or privacy alerts.
sub_tasks.validation_criteria: No error budget impact after 24h canary.

sub_tasks.description: Roll out 100%. Close ticket after 48h of stable metrics.
sub_tasks.validation_criteria: Dashboards show ≥98% of HTTP spans with the new attributes when headers present.

contextual_hints: Locate the exact layer where OTLP spans are finalized (server and client sides may differ) and verify header availability at that point in the pipeline
Capture and propagate HTTP_RESPONSE_REDIRECT_LOCATION which exists only for 3xx responses and may be mutated by intermediate middleware
Validate that header collection complies with existing header-scrubbing / GDPR redaction logic

test_requirements: Integration tests for telemetry data collection

result.explanation:
OpenTelemetry spans for inbound HTTP requests currently miss two important attributes:
• `http.referer` – the value of the incoming `Referer` request header  
• `http.response.redirect_location` – the value of the `Location` header sent back with 3xx responses  

The global `ScmHttpApplication` already runs for every request inside the classic ASP.NET stack, which is also where the OpenTelemetry `Activity` for the request is active (`Activity.Current`).  
By enriching that `Activity` before the request is processed (for the *Referer*) and right after the response is written (for the redirect *Location*), we guarantee the two attributes are always present when the corresponding header exists.

			{

				Exception,				// Some sort of exception -- nothing the user can really do about it
				ExpiredTrial,			// The user's trial account has expired
				FileTooLarge,			// The user is not allowed to upload files this large.
				Guest,					// The user is a guest (and thus cannot upload files)
				InsufficientSpace,		// The user doesn't have sufficient space to upload this file (not currently used)
				InvalidCredentials,	// The user failed to login with a valid username or password.
				InvalidDocument,		// The document does not exist
				InvalidFolder,			// The folder does not exist
				ReadOnlyDocument,		// The document exists, but is readonly
				ReadOnlyFolder,		// The folder exists, but is readonly
				ResendChunk,			// Part of the file needs to be resent.
				ResendFile,			// The entire file needs to be resent.
				TooManyFailures,		// The server is aborting the upload because of too many failures
				TooManyFiles 			// The user has already uploaded too many files (not currently used)
			}

			public enum Legacy
			{
				Unset = 0,				// Unset, of course.  This should never occur.
				Exception,				// Some sort of exception -- nothing the user can really do about it
				ExpiredTrial,			// The user's trial account has expired
				FileTooLarge,			// The user is not allowed to upload files this large.
				Guest,					// The user is a guest (and thus cannot upload files)
				InsufficientSpace,		// The user doesn't have sufficient space to upload this file (not currently used)
				InvalidCredentials,	// The user failed to login with a valid username or password.
				ResendChunk,			// Part of the file needs to be resent.
				ResendFile,			// The entire file needs to be resent.
				TooManyFailures,		// The server is aborting the upload because of too many failures
				TooManyFiles, 			// The user has already uploaded too many files (not currently used)
				NoPrivilege             // The user does not have enough privileges for the requested operation
			}

		public const string ENUM_RESOURCE_FORMAT = "enum_{0}_{1}"; // 0 is the name of the enum 1 is a member: enum_YesNoDefault_Yes
		/// <summary>
		/// Returns the string defined in the given resource manager as "enum_EnumName_FieldName". For example "enum_UserRole_Primary".
		/// Falls back to GetName(Enum).
		/// </summary>
		public static string GetLocalizedName(Enum e, ResourceManager rm)
		{
			string enumResourceKeyName = string.Format(ENUM_RESOURCE_FORMAT, e.GetType().Name, e);
			string loc = null;
			if (null != rm)
			{
				loc = rm.GetString(enumResourceKeyName);
			}
			if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(loc))
			{
				try
				{
					// Other projects (reporting) can't really reference these resources, so the attempt will throw. We silently ignore it
					// and let it fall through and pick up the string from the description attribute of the enum.
					loc = Resources.CoreTypes.ResourceManager.GetString(enumResourceKeyName);
				}
				catch
				{
				}

			}
			if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(loc))
				return loc;

			// Just adding a track of the enums not found, we should check the logs for '[I18N|Error]' instances
			// Default File: wherever/san/logs/atlas/{MachineName}/app.txt
			_log.WarnNoPII("[I18N|Error] EnumLocalizedName not found: " + enumResourceKeyName);
			return GetName(e);
		}

		/// <summary>
		/// Returns a sorted list all the constants defined in an enum. The key is the name, on which it is sorted
		/// and the value is the int for the constant.
		/// Can filter the return list on the enum value based on the predicate.
		/// Good for drop down list on the UI
		/// </summary>
		public static SortedList<string, int> GetLocalizedNames(Type enumType, ResourceManager rm, Func<int, bool> predicate = null)
		{
			SortedList<string, int> nv = new SortedList<string, int>();
			MemberInfo[] members = enumType.GetMembers(BindingFlags.DeclaredOnly | BindingFlags.Public | BindingFlags.Static);
			for (int ndx = 0; ndx < members.Length; ndx++)
			{
				Enum e = (Enum)Enum.Parse(enumType, members[ndx].Name);
				int intval = Convert.ToInt32(e);
				if (null != predicate && !predicate.Invoke(intval))
					continue;
				nv.Add(GetLocalizedName(e, rm), intval);
			}
			return nv;
		}

		/// <summary>
		/// Use reflection to find if the Description attribute was made for this enum value.
		/// If one exists, return that value.  This is what allows us to rename Enums.UserRole
		/// members willynilly.
		/// If none exists, then we return the simple ToString.
		/// </summary>
		public static string GetName(Enum e)
		{
			// Use reflection to find the appropriate Description attribute.
			// If no description attribute exists, just return role.ToString().
			// Concept taken from here: http://blogs.msdn.com/abhinaba/archive/2005/10/20/483000.aspx
			MemberInfo[] memInfo = e.GetType().GetMember(e.ToString());
			if (memInfo != null && memInfo.Length > 0)
			{
				object[] attrs = memInfo[0].GetCustomAttributes(typeof(DescriptionAttribute), false);
				if (attrs != null && attrs.Length > 0) return ((DescriptionAttribute)attrs[0]).Description;
			}

			return e.ToString();
		}

		public static string GetUserRoleString(UserRole userRole, UserRoleNameType nameType, CultureInfo cultureInfo = null)
		{
			Dictionary<UserRole, string> dictionary = new Dictionary<UserRole, string>();
			switch (nameType)
			{
				case UserRoleNameType.Classic:
					dictionary = ClassicUserRoleStrings(cultureInfo);
					break;
				case UserRoleNameType.CLM:
					dictionary = ClmUserRoleStrings(cultureInfo);
					break;
				case UserRoleNameType.MixedMode:
					dictionary = ClmMixedModeUserRoleStrings(cultureInfo);
					break;
			}

			if (dictionary.ContainsKey(userRole))
			{
				return dictionary[userRole];
			}

			return string.Empty;
		}

		/// <summary>
		/// Use reflection to find if the Description attribute was made for this enum value.
		/// If one exists, return that value.  This is what allows us to rename Enums.UserRole
		/// members willynilly.
		/// If none exists, then we return the simple ToString.
		/// Created by DK but basically made the above function return all of the members.
		/// </summary>
		public static string[] GetNames(Type enumType)
		{
			// Use reflection to find the appropriate Description attribute.
			// If no description attribute exists, just return role.ToString().
			// Concept taken from here: http://blogs.msdn.com/abhinaba/archive/2005/10/20/483000.aspx

			// Get static members declared on this class only; we don't want ToString(), CompareTo(), etc.
			MemberInfo[] members = enumType.GetMembers(BindingFlags.DeclaredOnly | BindingFlags.Public | BindingFlags.Static);
			List<string> arl = new List<string>();
			if (members != null && members.Length > 0)
			{
				foreach (MemberInfo memInfo in members)
				{
					object[] attrs = memInfo.GetCustomAttributes(typeof(DescriptionAttribute), false);
					if (attrs != null && attrs.Length > 0)
					{
						arl.Add(((DescriptionAttribute)attrs[0]).Description);
					}
					else
					{
						arl.Add(memInfo.Name);
					}
				}
			}

			return arl.ToArray();
		}


		public static Dictionary<long, string> GetUserRoleNameValues(UserRoleNameType nameType)
		{
			Dictionary<long, string> values = new Dictionary<long, string>();
			Dictionary<UserRole, string> dictionary = new Dictionary<UserRole, string>();
			switch (nameType)
			{
				case UserRoleNameType.Classic:
					dictionary = ClassicUserRoleStrings();
					break;
				case UserRoleNameType.CLM:
					dictionary = ClmUserRoleStrings();
					break;
				case UserRoleNameType.MixedMode:
					dictionary = ClmMixedModeUserRoleStrings();
					break;
			}

			foreach (KeyValuePair<UserRole, string> valuePair in dictionary)
			{
				values.Add((long) valuePair.Key, valuePair.Value);
			}

			return values;
		}


		/// <summary>
		/// Use reflection to find the role required for this enum.
		/// If none exists, then we return not set... which will have to be handled
		/// in uses of this function.
		/// </summary>
		public static UserRole GetRoleRequired(Enum e)
		{
			//get the reflected member and then get the custom attribute of the member
			MemberInfo[] memInfo = e.GetType().GetMember(e.ToString());
			if (memInfo != null && memInfo.Length > 0)
			{
				object[] attrs = memInfo[0].GetCustomAttributes(typeof(RoleRequired), false);
				if (attrs != null && attrs.Length > 0) return ((RoleRequired)attrs[0]).Required;
			}

			//RoleRequired attribute was not set
			return UserRole.NotSet;
		}

		/// <summary>
		/// This makes things easier to lookup all of the values an enum has.
		///
		/// IMPORTANT the key is the value not the name of the enum.
		/// </summary>
		/// <param name="e"></param>
		/// <returns></returns>
		public static NameValueCollection GetNVC(Enum e)
		{
			// create at the beginning so that it always send a NVC even if it is empty
			NameValueCollection nvc = new NameValueCollection();

			//Load all of the enum names Uses enum w/out the s
			string[] names = Enum.GetNames(e.GetType());

			// put the roles in a namevaluecollection for easy access later
			foreach (string name in names)
			{
				//parse back from the name to the actual enum
				Enum next = (Enum)Enum.Parse(e.GetType(), name, true);
				if (next != null)
					nvc.Add(Convert.ToInt32(next).ToString(), GetName(next));
			}

			return nvc;
		}

		private static readonly ConcurrentDictionary<Type, IReadOnlyDictionary<int, string>> EnumDictionaryCache = new ConcurrentDictionary<Type, IReadOnlyDictionary<int, string>>();
		public static IReadOnlyDictionary<int, string> ToDictionary<T>()
		{
			var type = typeof(T);
			if (!type.IsEnum)
				throw new ArgumentException("Type must be an enum");

			return EnumDictionaryCache.GetOrAdd(type, _ => Enum.GetValues(type)
				.Cast<T>()
				.ToDictionary(@enum => (int) (object) @enum, @enum =>
					type.GetMember(@enum.ToString())[0].GetCustomAttributes(typeof(DescriptionAttribute), false)
						.OfType<DescriptionAttribute>()
						.FirstOrDefault()?.Description ?? @enum.ToString()));
		}

		public static bool TryGetValueFromDescription<T>(string description, out T value, StringComparison stringCompare = StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase)
		{
			var type = typeof(T);
			if (!type.IsEnum)
				throw new ArgumentException();

			value = default(T);
			if (description == null)
				return false;

			foreach (var field in type.GetFields())
			{
				var attribute = Attribute.GetCustomAttribute(field,
					typeof(DescriptionAttribute)) as DescriptionAttribute;
				if (attribute != null && attribute.Description.Equals(description, stringCompare))
				{
					value = (T) field.GetValue(null);
					return true;
				}
				if (field.Name == description)
				{
					value = (T) field.GetValue(null);
					return true;
				}
			}

			return false;
		}

		public static bool TryGetUserRoleFromStringValue(string roleString, UserRoleNameType nameType, out UserRole role, CultureInfo cultureInfo = null)
		{

			Dictionary<UserRole, string> dictionary = new Dictionary<UserRole, string>();
			role = UserRole.NotSet;
			switch (nameType)
			{
				case UserRoleNameType.Classic:
					dictionary = ClassicUserRoleStrings(cultureInfo);
					break;
				case UserRoleNameType.CLM:
					dictionary = ClmUserRoleStrings(cultureInfo);
					break;
				case UserRoleNameType.MixedMode:
					dictionary = ClmMixedModeUserRoleStrings(cultureInfo);
					break;
			}

			if (dictionary.Any(x => x.Value.Equals(roleString, StringComparison.InvariantCultureIgnoreCase)))
			{
				role = dictionary
					.FirstOrDefault(x => x.Value.Equals(roleString, StringComparison.InvariantCultureIgnoreCase)).Key;
				return true;
			}

			return false;
		}


		public static bool TryParse<T>(string value, out T result)
		{
			bool ok = false;

			try
			{
				result = (T)Enum.Parse(typeof(T), value, true);
				if (typeof(T).GetCustomAttributes(typeof(FlagsAttribute), false).Any())
					ok = true; // no checking if invalid flags are set
				else
					ok = Enum.IsDefined(typeof(T), result);
			}
			catch
			{
				result = default(T);
			}

			return ok;
		}

		public static string GetStringValue(Enum linkBehavior)
		{
			string output;
			Type type = linkBehavior.GetType();
			FieldInfo fi = type.GetField(linkBehavior.ToString());
			StringValue[] attrs = fi.GetCustomAttributes(typeof(StringValue), false) as StringValue[];
			if (attrs.Length > 0)
			{
				output = attrs[0].Value;
			}
			else
			{
				output = linkBehavior.ToString();
			}
			return output;
		}

		public static Dictionary<string, int> ToStringIntDictionary<T>()
		{
			var values = Enum.GetValues(typeof(T)).Cast<int>();
			return values.ToDictionary(value => Enum.GetName(typeof(T), value));
		}

		{
			private string _value;

			public StringValue(string value)
			{
				_value = value;
			}

			public string Value
			{
				get { return _value; }
